  "response": "As of October 2023, here are some of the best smartphones under \u20b912,000 in India, offering good value for money in terms of performance, camera, battery, and overall user experience:\n\n### 1. **Redmi 12 (4GB RAM + 128GB Storage)**  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - 6.79\" FHD+ 90Hz display  \n     - MediaTek Helio G88 processor  \n     - 50MP triple camera setup  \n     - 5000mAh battery with 18W fast charging  \n     - Android 13 with MIUI 14  \n   - **Pros**: Good display, decent performance, large battery.  \n   - **Price**: Around \u20b911,999  \n\n### 2. **Realme Narzo 50i Prime (4GB RAM + 64GB Storage)**  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - 6.5\" HD+ display  \n     - Unisoc T612 processor  \n     - 8MP rear camera  \n     - 5000mAh battery with 10W charging  \n     - Android 12 with Realme UI S  \n   - **Pros**: Affordable, decent battery life, lightweight design.  \n   - **Price**: Around \u20b97,499  \n\n### 3. **Samsung Galaxy M14 5G (4GB RAM + 128GB Storage)**  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - 6.6\" FHD+ 90Hz display  \n     - Exynos 1330 5G processor  \n     - 50MP triple camera setup  \n     - 6000mAh battery with 25W fast charging  \n     - Android 13 with One UI Core 5.1  \n   - **Pros**: 5G support, excellent battery life, reliable software.  \n   - **Price**: Around \u20b911,990  \n\n### 4. **Tecno Spark 10C (4GB RAM + 64GB Storage)**  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - 6.6\" HD+ display  \n     - MediaTek Helio G37 processor  \n     - 50MP dual camera setup  \n     - 5000mAh battery with 18W fast charging  \n     - Android 13 with HiOS 12.6  \n   - **Pros**: Good cameras, sleek design, affordable.  \n   - **Price**: Around \u20b98,999  \n\n### 5. **Poco C55 (4GB RAM + 64GB Storage)**  \n   - **Key Features**:  \n     - 6.71\" HD+ display  \n     - MediaTek Helio G85 processor  \n     - 50MP dual camera setup  \n     - 5000mAh battery with 10W charging  \n     - Android 12 with MIUI 13  \n   - **Pros**: Decent performance, good battery life, affordable.  \n   - **Price**: Around \u20b99,499  \n\n### Recommendations:\n- **Best Overall**: **Redmi 12** - Offers a great balance of display, performance, and battery life.  \n- **Best for 5G**: **Samsung Galaxy M14 5G** - Future-proof with 5G support and a massive battery.  \n- **Budget Pick**: **Realme Narzo 50i Prime** - Perfect for basic usage at an affordable price.  \n\nConsider your priorities (display, battery, performance, or camera) before choosing. Prices may vary depending on offers and discounts, so check platforms like Flipkart, Amazon, and the brand's official website for the best deals.",
